# Timeline Replay Heatmap System

This report describes the architecture, implementation, and integration of the **Timeline Replay Heatmap System** into the **AI Command Center for Bengaluru Traffic Police** project for the Flipkart Gridlock Hackathon.

---

## 1. System Architecture

The Timeline Replay Heatmap System parses historical incident logs, filters them dynamically based on active hours (4 PM to 8 PM), maps the severity using a custom color-gradient scheme, and animates the spatial evolution of city-wide gridlock.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Timeline Slider / Play Button] --> B[Hour Selection: 16:00 - 20:00]
    B -->|Check start_hour <= select <= end_hour| C[Filter Active Incident Logs]
    C --> D[Compute Cumulative Metrics]
    D -->|Active Alerts, Avg Delay, Police Deployed| E[KPI Dashboard Panels]
    C --> F[Generate Heatmap Matrix]
    F -->|Green/Yellow/Red Gradient| G[Folium Map Visualization]
```

---

